		The second, by Voets et al., deals with programs that contain propagation. 
		It is however less powerful on programs without propagation. 
		In this paper, we present new termination conditions 
		that are strictly more powerful than those from previous approaches 
		and that are also applicable to a new class of programs. 
		Furthermore, we present a new representation for CHR states 
