	year = {2007},
	month = mar,
	number = {CW 480},
	abstract = {
	This paper investigates the relationship between the Logical Algorithms language (LA) 
	of Ganzinger and McAllester and Constraint Handling Rules (CHR).
	 We present a translation scheme from LA to CHR-rp: 
	CHR with rule priorities and show that the meta-complexity theorem for LA can be applied to a subset of CHR-rp via inverse translation.
	This result is compared with previous work. 
	Inspired by the high-level implementation proposal of Ganzinger and McAllester, 
	we demonstrate how LA programs can be compiled into CHR rules that interact with a scheduler written in CHR. 
	This forms the first actual implementation of LA. 
	Our implementation achieves the complexity required for the meta-complexity theorem to hold 
	and can execute a subset of CHR-rp with strong complexity bounds. 
	},
